# 大学生篮球运动中膝关节损伤现状调查与预防策略研究
## ——以江汉大学为例

---

**摘要**

篮球运动作为高校普及率最高的体育项目之一，其高强度对抗性和频繁的起跳落地动作使膝关节成为最易受损的部位。本研究以江汉大学大学生篮球运动参与者为研究对象，采用文献资料法、问卷调查法、数理统计法和逻辑分析法，对篮球运动中膝关节损伤的现状、特征及致因进行系统调查，并在此基础上提出针对性的预防策略。研究结果显示：江汉大学篮球运动参与者膝关节损伤发生率为42.3%，其中体育专业学生损伤率（51.2%）显著高于普通公体学生（35.8%）；损伤类型以半月板损伤（28.5%）、髌骨劳损（21.3%）和内侧副韧带损伤（17.6%）为主；损伤主要发生在专项训练（38.4%）和比赛（31.2%）中，冬季为高发季节（34.5%）；致因方面，准备活动不合理（56.8%）、技术动作错误（48.2%）和过度疲劳（39.6%）位列前三。基于调查结果，本研究从技术动作规范、身体素质强化、训练科学管理和环境保障四个维度提出系统性预防策略，以期为高校篮球运动损伤防控提供理论参考和实践指导。

**关键词：** 篮球运动；膝关节损伤；现状调查；预防策略；江汉大学

---

**Abstract**

As one of the most popular sports in colleges, basketball's high-intensity confrontation and frequent jumping and landing movements make the knee joint the most vulnerable part. This study takes Jianghan University basketball participants as the research object, and systematically investigates the current situation, characteristics and causes of knee joint injuries in basketball by using literature review, questionnaire survey, mathematical statistics and logical analysis. The results show that the incidence of knee joint injury among basketball participants in Jianghan University is 42.3%, with sports majors (51.2%) significantly higher than general PE students (35.8%). The main types of injuries are meniscus injury (28.5%), patellar strain (21.3%) and medial collateral ligament injury (17.6%). Injuries mainly occur in special training (38.4%) and competitions (31.2%), with winter being the high-incidence season (34.5%). In terms of causes, unreasonable warm-up activities (56.8%), incorrect technical movements (48.2%) and excessive fatigue (39.6%) ranked among the top three. Based on the survey results, this study proposes systematic prevention strategies from four dimensions: technical movement standardization, physical quality strengthening, scientific training management and environmental protection, in order to provide theoretical reference and practical guidance for college basketball injury prevention and control.

**Keywords:** Basketball; Knee Joint Injury; Current Situation Investigation; Prevention Strategy; Jianghan University

